of its warm, tropical climate close to the Andes. This weather also brings cooler nights and a fair amount of rain, although this usually is only for a few hours at night.&#xA0;&#xA0;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Book your trip between December and March if you want to visit in the driest months (Medellin summertime). Alternatively, come to the city during fun festivals&#x2014;for example, the Festival of Flowers in August. This famous festival draws Colombians from all over the country; make sure to book your trip in advance!<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"block-link block-link--hotels\">\n                <div class=\"block-link__container\">\n\n                    <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                        <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--hotels\"><\/span>\n                        <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                    <\/div>\n\n                    <p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/go\/hotels-medellin\/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Here are all your hotel options in Medellin.<\/a><\/p>\n\n                <\/div>\n            <\/div>\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/12170428\/medellin-colombia-20.jpg\" alt=\"Castle Museum medellin colombia\"><\/noscript><img width=\"226\" height=\"338\" alt=\"Castle Museum medellin colombia\" class=\"wp-image-83768 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1281px) 100vw, 1281px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/12170428\/medellin-colombia-20.jpg 1281w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/12170428\/medellin-colombia-20-400x600.jpg 400w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/12170428\/medellin-colombia-20-540x810.jpg 540w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/12170428\/medellin-colombia-20-226x338.jpg 226w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/12170428\/medellin-colombia-20-20x30.jpg 20w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/12170428\/medellin-colombia-20-109x163.jpg 109w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/12170428\/medellin-colombia-20-120x180.jpg 120w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/12170428\/medellin-colombia-20-512x768.jpg 512w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/12170428\/medellin-colombia-20-683x1024.jpg 683w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/12170428\/medellin-colombia-20-721x1080.jpg 721w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/12170428\/medellin-colombia-20-961x1440.jpg 961w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/12170428\/medellin-colombia-20-300x450.jpg 300w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/12170428\/medellin-colombia-20-600x899.jpg 600w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/12170428\/medellin-colombia-20-150x225.jpg 150w\" tempsrc=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/12170428\/medellin-colombia-20-20x30.jpg\" src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png\" onerror=\"this.srcset='https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.src='https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.classList.remove('lazypreload'); \"><a class=\"pinit\" href=\"https:\/\/www.pinterest.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-pin=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/12170428\/medellin-colombia-20.jpg\">Save<\/a><\/div><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-safety-in-medellin-colombia\">Safety in Medellin, Colombia<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The famous saying in Colombia is &#x2018;no dar papaya&#x2019; meaning &#x2018;don&#x2019;t give papaya&#x2019;. This saying doesn&#x2019;t really have anything to do with fruit; it&#x2019;s more about not allowing anyone to scam you. These days, Medellin is safe, but people are still looking to take advantage, so it&#x2019;s always good to be alert. For example:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Know your neighborhoods.<\/li><li>Stay in the touristy areas where there is more police presence.<\/li><li>In busy areas, be careful of your bags as pickpocketing is common.<\/li><li>When sitting down, put your arm or leg through your belongings so no one can swipe them from under the table.<\/li><li>Leave your valuables locked up in the hotel or guesthouse.<\/li><li>Don&#x2019;t put your phone or wallet in your back pocket.<\/li><li>Try to look where you&#x2019;re going ahead of time instead of getting out your phone to look at maps.<\/li><li>Don&#x2019;t go down dark, quiet, unlit streets late at night.<\/li><li>Always trust your intuition. If something doesn&#x2019;t feel right, it usually isn&#x2019;t.<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n<div class=\"block-link block-link--readmore \">\n                <div class=\"block-link__container\">\n\n                    <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                        <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--readmore\"><\/span>\n                        <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                    <\/div>\n\n                    <p><strong>Read:<\/strong> <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/tips\/travel-safety\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">How to Travel Safe<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n                <\/div>\n            <\/div><\/div><\/div>\n\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"Things to do in Medellin In Medellin, Colombia, you can be walking among towering skyscrapers, enjoying a coffee on the terrace of a chic sky bar in the morning. By afternoon, you can be flying in a gondola over the dense forest and traditional villages. Some of t